The paper deals with influence propagation in social networks, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of several CS sub-fields. The paper also involves optimization problems, which could place it under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.CY (Computational Geometry). The use of machine learning or AI techniques is not explicitly mentioned, but it is possible that they are used in the proposed algorithms, which could place the paper under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper deals with real-world scenarios and empirical tests, which could place it under cs.SOC (Computational Social Science).
